I've added try-catch blocks to both route handlers. Errors are now passed to Express's error middleware via `next(err)`. You should also add an error middleware in your main app file:

```typescript
app.use((err: Error, req: Request, res: Response, next: NextFunction) => {
  console.error(err.stack);
  res.status(500).json({ error: 'Internal server error' });
});
```
